  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "45uewUwRN0zdZkIpkXDMoUa89Mo=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## `adapter/src/` root (infrastructure kept from previous plugin)\n\n```\nadapter/src/\n  swarm-client.ts           - Bee API: /bytes, /bzz, feeds, ACT, PSS, GSOC, node status\n  swarm-crypto.ts           - AES-256-GCM encryption\n  wallet-signer.ts          - Key derivation from wallet signature\n  stamp-manager.ts          - Postage stamp lifecycle + CoinGecko pricing\n  share-manager.ts          - Cross-user ACT sharing + public profile I/O\n  folder-tree.ts            - Recursive tree builder\n  types.ts                  - Manifest, sharing (ACT v2), stamp status\n  swarm-operation-store.ts  - IOperationStore interface\n  swarm-keyframe-store.ts   - IKeyframeStore interface\n  bytes-utils.ts            - hex/bytes conversion\n```\n\n### Role\n\nThese modules are **infrastructure** \u2014 they pre-date the channel-based sync architecture but are still used underneath it.\n\n- `swarm-client.ts` is the single Bee wrapper; everything above it goes through this client.\n- `stamp-manager.ts` handles postage stamp purchase, top-up, and USD pricing.\n- `share-manager.ts` abstracts ACT grantee management for the chat and document-share flows.\n- `swarm-operation-store.ts` and `swarm-keyframe-store.ts` expose `IOperationStore` / `IKeyframeStore` interfaces \u2014 the contract between the channel layer and persistent Swarm storage.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:27.000Z"
    }
  },
